RACE.RACE_TEXT: EMERALD DOWNS RACE 1 6F Dirt CR: 54. Maiden Claiming Purse 8500. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: OUR GIRL ASHLEY broke out to bump ZEVA DEE, then steadied in tight between horses nearing the five-eights pole, swung out to move forward on the turn while racing four-wide, continued wide into the stretch and was up in the final sixteenth. SENSUOUS KITTY prompted the pace while racing two-wide, took the lead from ZEVA DEE inside the eighth pole but was unable to hold off the winner. ZEVA DEE was bumped at the start by OUR GIRL ASHLEY, then saved ground setting the pace into the stretch and tired late. LUTE'S DIAMOND was allowed to settle while racing two-wide but lacked a rally. DEBBI'S TALON was prominent early while racing three-wide and tired. HASTA LUEGO saved ground chasing the pace for a half mile and gave way. THE STEWARDS CONDUCTED AN INQUIRY INTO THE START BUT AFTER VIEWING THE FILMS MADE NO CHANGE IN THE ORDER OF FINISH.

ENTRY.COMMENT: broke out, bumped, in tight 5/8, 4-wide turn, up final 1/16

ENTRY.NAME: Zeva Dee
ENTRY.OWNER: White Diamond Syndicate and Cissell Jeff

RACE.FOOTNOTES: GOLD RUSH JUNIOR prompted the issue while racing four-wide on the turn, took the lead nearing the quarter pole, opened clear nearing the eighth pole and maintained a safe advantage. THE THIRD RING vied for the lead from along inside, dropped back slightly on the turn, then responded during the drive and came again to earn the place in a game try. GYPSY GUN was forwardly placed while racing six-wide on the turn, angled in during the drive to offer a bid nearing the eighth pole and flattened out late. HOLLYWOOD AS USUAL vied for the early lead from along the inside, was shuffled back nearing the half mile pole in tight along the inside, angled out to be four-wide entering the stretch, was in tight briefly nearing the three-sixteenths pole and then finished willingly when clear. AGRIGENTO dueled for the lead to the stretch from between horse while two-wide and weakened. TIME 'N TIME AGAIN was unhurried early, came seven-wide into the stretch and failed to menace.
